ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04808/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04808/canvas/1/d408eef9-793f-41b5-ada5-4680ff8622e3","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T19:10:40.902Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Unlike Alma, who looks over at Reynolds, the latter stays focused on his book. Although his gaze dictates a great deal of their relationship and, consequently, the plot of the film, he’s here seen not paying attention. As Alma observes him and, in the previous scene, accidentally learns about the poisonous mushrooms, he fails to really see Alma for who she is. The result will be a clash of wills.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04808/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:737.3285173559823,135.90980428360405,433.82085487444624,524.0721935007386"}}}]}]}]}